				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/peppersghost" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1553042); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1553042&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610226190" alt="PeppersGhost" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1553042)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/peppersghost" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1553042); return false;" >PeppersGhost</a></span> <span class="odate time_1519088306 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">20 Feb 2018 00:58</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3715838">
									

<p>There's a lot to love here. The presentation of Night as a nigh-unstoppable force of death is fitting, and it's good to see <a href="/scp-982">SCP-982</a> formally tied to the growing Spirit mythos.</p>
<p>That said, it's the Pillston death that really sells this one for me. It gives Night some added characterization and keeps the piece grounded. Spooky murders are not uncommon in the SCP universe, but Pillston's demise is a nice reminder that we're dealing with the anomalous mob here.</p>

							</div>

								
					
